     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The southern Brisbane suburb that multicultural families and investors pursue for its elevated residential character, shopping centre amenity, strong rental demand, and proximity to the Sunnybank food precinct.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Sunnybank Hills sits approximately fourteen kilometres south of the Brisbane CBD, occupying elevated ground in Brisbane's southern residential corridor that gives the suburb a settled character distinct from the flatter land around it. The suburb has built its appeal on three overlapping foundations: its own retail and commercial hub around Sunnybank Hills Shoppingtown, its proximity to the nationally recognised Sunnybank food precinct a short drive north, and its position in a corridor with direct Pacific Motorway access that connects residents to the CBD and the Gold Coast. Buyers in 2026 who target Sunnybank Hills have typically done deliberate suburb comparisons and concluded that the combination of community character, amenity, and price point is genuine value in Brisbane's southern market.
    </p>
