    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Sunnybank Hills?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Sunnybank Hills values are driven by its position in the southern corridor with direct Pacific Motorway access, proximity to Sunnybank Hills Shoppingtown and the Sunnybank food precinct, the suburb's established family character, and consistent demand from both owner-occupiers and investors. Properties with workable outdoor space, functional family layouts, and quiet street positions consistently attract the strongest competition. The suburb's dual appeal to families and investors creates a deeper buyer pool than single-demographic suburbs at a comparable distance from the CBD.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Sunnybank Hills?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Sunnybank Hills homes typically sell within 26 to 40 days. The suburb's buyer pool spans multicultural families, investors, and buyers comparing it against neighbouring Sunnybank and Runcorn. Buyers who target this corridor specifically tend to act with confidence when a property is correctly priced and presents cleanly. Correct pricing against recent comparables, combined with presentation that speaks directly to the suburb's predominant buyer types, is the primary lever for a faster campaign.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Sunnybank Hills?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Sunnybank Hills offers a family-oriented, community-connected lifestyle about fourteen kilometres south of the Brisbane CBD. Sunnybank Hills Shoppingtown provides everyday retail and dining, and the Sunnybank food precinct adds a culinary destination that residents genuinely value. Pacific Motorway access keeps the CBD and Gold Coast within practical commuting range. The suburb's established streets, parks, and low-turnover owner-occupier base give it a settled residential character that families find hard to replicate in newer outer-ring developments at a comparable price.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Sunnybank Hills a good suburb to invest in?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Sunnybank Hills has consistently attracted investor attention for its combination of strong rental demand, a deep and active resale buyer pool, and a suburb identity that the southern corridor's multicultural communities value and understand. The suburb's proximity to Sunnybank amenity, motorway access, and established community infrastructure create tenant demand that is steady across economic conditions. Investors who understand the specific driver of demand in this corridor make better decisions about property selection, preparation, and long-term hold strategy.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

